description.narrative: (West Bank and Gaza): In FY 2014 USAID will invest $16,000,000 in the Palestinian Community Assistance Program (PCAP) to: 1) support economic recovery and development in Gaza through the creation of income generation and business development opportunities; and 2) address social recovery needs through improvements in education and health. The primary project components of PCAP include: (1) promoting food security and economic growth through home garden production, Information and Communication Technology (ICT) enterprise development, and skills training; and (2) maintaining social cohesion and recovery through community outreach programs focused on mental well-being, childhood education, humanitarian assistance, and cash-for-work programs. Key results expected under PCAP in FY 2014 include: provision of social assistance and services to 105,967 people in Gaza including 49,348 women, creation of 116,436 workdays of employment, 3,570 children participating in accelerated learning and after school programs and another 3,520 children receiving emotional well-being support, more than 4,125 individuals trained in improved agricultural production techniques, and 110 internships provided to fresh graduates.
